		<b>Comment By joshuezzes, 12-10-09</b>
		<p>Do any Free Reverse Cell Phone Directories exist? <br />
<br />
Many people ask this question when searching for a free reverse cell phone directory online.  However, no such thing exists! A small fee is to be expected if you're looking to receive complete and accurate information. <br />
<br />
You may find some free websites which claim to offer a free reverse trace of a cellphone number, but you'll find most of these will only inform you of the phone's service or the location at which the phone number was issued, never the current owner of that number. <br />
<br />
Why Doesn't A Free Reverse Cell Phone Directory Exist? <br />
<br />
So, the big question is, why isn't there such a thing as a free reverse cell phone directory, especially once people realize one does not exist yet? There do exist, after all, many free reverse lookup directories for traditional land line phone numbers. So why is it different for cell phones? <br />
<br />
Well, the information behind cell phone numbers and land line numbers are classified differently. It's long be true that your home phone number is considered public domain. After all, does the phone book need your permission to list your home phone number? In fact, you often have to pay money simply to keep your number from being listed! <br />
<br />
Cell phone services providers charge for every phone call you receive, it's because of this that the numbers are considered more private. This also makes these numbers harder to trace. <br />
<br />
411 Wireless Directory <br />
<br />
A public reverse cell phone directory was in the talk some years ago. The various cell phone service providers would have placed the numbers of their customers in this directory and it would be publicly available. Concerns over privacy and invasion from telemarketers put a stop to this idea, at least for the time being. <br />
<br />
However this doesn't mean such a directory is impossible. It can, and already has, been done! These directories take a lot of time and effort to organized, they require information from millions of records to be added manually. Such a gargantuan effort simply can't be offered for free. However, even many directories which carry such a fee do not possess a complete database of information. <br />
<br />
However, by far the most complete and accurate reverse cell phone directory is Trace Cell Number. Search Trace Cell Number on Google and you'll soon see it's often touted as the highest ranking reverse cell phone directory available on the internet. <br />
<br />
